4. Narpulate(x,z): Possible. If z is part of x and touches x's boundary, this is consistent with y being part of z and touching both boundaries.

5. Zindlequack(x,z): Not possible. If z is part of x and y is part of z, then y touches x's boundary (from Narpulate(x,y)), which means z must also touch x's boundary.

6. Frooblenap(x,z): Possible. If x and z are coincident, then y is part of both and touches the boundary of both.
